full_text: The purpose of this demo is to teach you how to create a personal auto submission. This is a modified version of the demonstration from the Policy Center Introduction course. If you already know how to create a personal auto submission, you may skip this demo. To create a personal auto submission in the base application, you need to start from a personal account, for example, Ray Newton. Click the down arrow next to search. Next, click Accounts. This is the Search Accounts screen. Click the First Name field. Type, Ray, into the First Name field. Click the Last Name field. Type, Newton, into the Last Name field. Click the Search button. Click the Account Number link for Ray Newton. This is the Account screen for Ray Newton. Next, we'll see how to create a personal auto submission. Click Actions. Click Actions. Click New Submission. This is the New Submission screen. The Organization, Producer Code, Quote Type, State, and Effective Date fields have default values. For the purposes of this demo, none of these need to be changed. We want to create a personal auto submission, so click the Select button next to Personal Auto. The first step is to select an Offerive. In Policy Center, an offering allows us to provide default coverages and it also can be used in Rating. Click the Offering Selection field. Select Basic Program. Click the Next button to move to the next step in the submission. This is the Policy Info screen. This is the Qualification screen. This screen asks a few questions to determine if the submission should proceed. For the purposes of this demo, we only need to select an answer for the first question. To do this, click the field next to the question, Is the Applicant Currently Insured? Select, Yes. Click the Next button to move to the next step in the submission. This is the Policy Info screen. Note the effective date of this policy. This will be used by the Rating Engine to select the correct rate book. Click the Next button to move to the next step in the submission. Here is the driver's screen. Click the Down arrow next to the Add button to add a driver. Click on Ray Newton in the existing driver. Now we can see the details of our driver Ray Newton. Nothing else needs to be changed on this screen. Click Next to move to the next step in the submission. The Vehicles screen is where a specific vehicle or vehicles to be insured are added. Click the Create Vehicle button. Click the VIN field. Click the VIN field. Type, 2 in the VIN field. Click the License Date field. Select California. Click the Cost New field. Type 25,000. Next, assign Ray Newton as a driver on this vehicle. Click the Down arrow next to the Add button. Click, Ray Newton. No other changes are needed on this screen. So click Next to move to the next step in this submission. Click this tab. Select the rental car loss of use coverage. Click next to move to the next step in this submission. This is the risk analysis screen. If there were any underwriting issues they would be listed here. There are none, so click next to move to the next step. This is the policy review screen. This screen shows details about the submission such as the effective date and selected coverages. Click the quote button to quote this submission. This is the quote screen. Note the total premium, taxes and surcharges that were calculated by the rating engine. The next step is to issue the policy. Click the bind options button. Click issue policy. Click, ok, on the confirmation message. This completes this demo.
